==English==
===Etymology===
[[real]] + [[world]]

===Noun===
'''real-world'''
#A pragmatic, a posteriori (as opposed to theoritical or academic) perpective, environment or solution.
#:''It's time to relocate this experiment from the laboratory into the '''real-world'''.''

===Adjective===
'''real-world'''
#Having a practicable, verifiable, non-academic quality.
#:''The moon rocket was a '''real-world''' application of astrophysics.''